# Type Safety & Immutability Law

## TYPE ASSERTION BAN — `as Type` IS FORBIDDEN IN BUSINESS LOGIC

Type assertions in business code are invisible to reviewers and break silently during refactors. All casts must go through auditable, greppable wrappers.

**[LAW] Type Assertion (`as`) Boundary:**
- **FORBIDDEN:** Domain/business data casting (e.g., `item as UserInfo`). Use typeCasters.
- **ALLOWED:** DOM event narrowing where no safer API exists (e.g., `e.target as HTMLInputElement`).

| FORBIDDEN | REQUIRED REPLACEMENT | Location |
|-----------|---------------------|----------|
| `value as Type` | `castValue<Type>(value)` | `@/utils/typeCasters` |
| `col as unknown as ColumnType` | `castColumn<ColumnType>(col)` | `@/utils/typeCasters` |
| `arr as unknown as U[]` | `castArray<T, U>(arr)` | `@/utils/typeCasters` |
| `obj as Record<string, unknown>` | `castRecord(obj)` | `@/utils/typeCasters` |
| `anything as any` | Refactor — always wrong | — |

❌ FORBIDDEN:
```typescript
const col = rawColumn as ColumnType          // invisible to reviewers, breaks silently
const record = data as Record<string, any>   // hides type errors, pollutes inferred types
```

✅ REQUIRED:
```typescript
import { castColumn, castRecord } from '@/utils/typeCasters'

const col = castColumn<ColumnType>(rawColumn)  // greppable, auditable, centralised
const record = castRecord(data)                // reviewable in one file
```

**Files where `as` IS permitted (limited exceptions):**
- `src/adapters/**`
- `src/utils/http/interceptors.ts`
- `src/utils/safeStorage/**`
- `src/utils/date/**`
- `src/components/UseEcharts/**`
- `src/hooks/modules/useChartTheme/**`

## `any` IS BANNED IN BUSINESS LOGIC

TypeScript `any` is forbidden in all of:
- `src/views/**`
- `src/components/**` (except `UseEcharts/`)
- `src/stores/**`
- `src/hooks/**` (except `useChartTheme/`)
- `src/api/**`

**Generic types must be preserved through all layers without degradation.**
`ApiResponse<UserInfo>` → `useHttpRequest<UserInfo>` → `data: Ref<UserInfo | undefined>`
Generics MUST NOT degrade to `unknown` or `any` across layer boundaries.

## IMMUTABILITY LAW — NEVER MUTATE SHARED OBJECTS IN PLACE

Direct mutation of shared objects, reactive state, or function arguments is **FORBIDDEN**.

| FORBIDDEN | REQUIRED REPLACEMENT | Location |
|-----------|---------------------|----------|
| `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(x))` | `deepClone(x)` | `@/utils/lodashes` |
| `Object.assign(target, source)` on reactive | `deepMerge(target, source)` or spread | `@/utils/lodashes` |
| `array.sort()` (mutates in place) | `[...arr].sort()` or `deepClone(arr).sort()` | Pure |
| `array.splice(i, 1)` | `arr.filter((_, idx) => idx !== i)` | Pure |
| `route.children = []` | `{ ...route, children: [] }` | Spread |
| `lodash.cloneDeep(x)` direct import | `deepClone(x)` | `@/utils/lodashes` |
| `lodash.isEqual(a, b)` direct import | `deepEqual(a, b)` | `@/utils/lodashes` |

❌ FORBIDDEN:
```typescript
const sorted = data.sort((a, b) => a.id - b.id)      // mutates original array!
const copy = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(complexObj))   // drops Dates, undefined, circular refs
Object.assign(reactiveObj, newProps)                  // bypasses Vue reactivity tracking
```

✅ REQUIRED:
```typescript
import { deepClone, deepMerge } from '@/utils/lodashes'

const sorted = [...data].sort((a, b) => a.id - b.id)  // pure — original untouched
const copy = deepClone(complexObj)                     // typed, handles edge cases
const merged = deepMerge({}, reactiveObj, newProps)    // non-destructive, reactive-safe
```

## DTO TRIPLE PATTERN — MANDATORY AT EVERY API BOUNDARY

Every `src/api/<module>/<feature>.ts` file MUST export three types. No exceptions.

```typescript
export interface DomainFeatureReq { ... }  // Request payload shape sent to the server
export interface DomainFeatureRes { ... }  // Raw response data shape from the server
export interface DomainFeatureDTO { ... }  // Transformed/enriched shape used by the app
```

- All API responses are wrapped in `ApiResponse<T>` — `{ code, message, data: T }`
- The Alova interceptor unwraps `data` — composables receive `T` directly, never the envelope
- `any` is FORBIDDEN in all DTO definitions

## TEMPLATE TYPE SAFETY — NO ASSERTIONS IN `<template>`

Type assertions are **FORBIDDEN** inside `<template>` blocks. The Vue compiler does not enforce TypeScript in templates; errors are silent.

❌ FORBIDDEN:
```vue
<template>
  <span>{{ (item as UserDTO).name }}</span>
</template>
```

✅ REQUIRED — narrow types in `<script setup>` via computed:
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { castValue } from '@/utils/typeCasters'
const userName = computed(() => castValue<UserDTO>(item).name)
</script>

<template>
  <span>{{ userName }}</span>
</template>
```
